  "ai_profile": "**Down The Rabbit Hole 2026: A Wonderland of Diversity and Discovery**  \n\nTaking place from July 3-5, *Down The Rabbit Hole 2026* promises an eclectic and boundary-pushing lineup of 194 artists, representing a vast array of genres and styles. From the pulsing beats of electronic, techno, and house (with 65 DJs on the roster) to the raw energy of indie rock, experimental sounds, and global music influences, the festival continues to be a melting pot of creativity. With notable contributions from electronic (29 artists), experimental (11), and hip-hop/rap (16 combined), the lineup offers something for every music lover.  \n\nThe festival’s commitment to diversity shines through in its representation of talent from 34 countries, including the Netherlands (71 artists), the UK (24), and the USA (15), as well as vibrant contributions from Brazil, South Korea, Nigeria, and DR Congo. Gender representation also stands out, with women, non-binary artists, and mixed-gender acts making up a significant portion of the lineup, alongside a commitment to showcasing artists of color (44 identified POC acts).  \n\nTrue to its name, *Down The Rabbit Hole* invites attendees to journey into the unexpected with a genre-bending mix of sounds, from Afrobeats and Anatolian rock to ambient jungle and baroque pop. This year’s edition underscores the festival’s ethos of inclusivity and innovation, making it a must-attend for those seeking fresh sounds, diverse voices, and a global perspective."
